  <title>GObject.Int64</title>
  <p>GObject.Int64 represents the <code>gint64</code> type in the GObject
  type system. You can pass this class object to methods taking a
  <link xref="GObject.Type"/>.
  </p>
  <p>A <code>gint64</code> value is an integer numeric value between
  -9223372036854775808 and 9223372036854775807, that is, a signed
  64 bit number.
  </p>
  <p>Note that because JS represents numbers in the double-precision
  floating point format, which only has 52 significant bits, converting
  to and from <code>gint64</code> may result in loss of precision.
  </p>
  <p>Creating a new object with <code>new GObject.Int64</code>
  returns a <code>Number</code> object with value 0.</p>
  <p>Calling <code>GObject.Int64(arg)</code> will coerce the argument to
  a number.</p>
